      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual convergence to 1e-6 for each load step; energy balance error < 0.1%.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear static analyses converged to force residual norm below 1e-6 for all load increments. Energy balance monitored throughout; maximum energy balance error 0.04%. Iterative solver (PCG with incomplete Cholesky preconditioning) tolerance set one order of magnitude tighter than acceptance criterion."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup by analyst not involved in original model construction; documented checklist completed.",
      "rationale": "Each of the three independent modeling teams (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) performed internal peer review of boundary conditions, material assignments, contact definitions, and load application. Cross-team comparison of input decks identified and resolved two minor discrepancies in fixture constraint representation prior to final analysis runs."
